(61, '10 factors affecting pregnant women’s sleeping', '10-factors-affecting-pregnant-womens-sleeping', 'Don Miller', '', '10 factors affecting pregnant women’s sleeping', 'Pregnant women often face the problems of insomnia. Here are some tips for any women in the period of pregnancy to improve the quality of sleeping to avoid and have a good health for them and their baby.', '<h3><strong>1.&#160;The bedroom spacy is airy</strong></h3>\r\nMedical experts say that the bedroom of pregnant women should be kept ventilating and air-conditioner needs to be limited for a long time. They can use electrics fans to purify air in the room which helps them to have the sensation of comfort when sleeping. The fresh environment is beneficial for the development of fetus.&#160;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/the-bedroom-spacy-is-airy.jpg" alt="The bedroom spacy is airy" width="403" height="478" /></div>\r\n<h3><strong>2. Wear night-clothes with larger size.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Women who are in the period of pregnant should wear night-clothes with larger size such as pajamas and any cotton fabric cloth to absorb sweat and drives them to feel comfortable when doing any activities.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/clothes-with-larger-size-for-pregnant-women.jpg" alt="Clothes with larger size for pregnant women" width="417" height="524" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>3.&#160;Have a shower before bed.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Bathing or soaking your food in warm water is highly recommended for pregnant women before going to bed. The degree of water ranges from 95 to 100,4 F which play an essential role of relaxing muscles, reducing fatigue and make them have stable psychology.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/pregnant-women-bathing.jpg" alt="Pregnant women bathing" width="500" height="300" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>4.&#160;Avoid wine or alcohol, instead of regularly drinking water before bed.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Wine is a stimulant which drives their mentality to euphoric and this condition is not a good thing to a good sleep. Moreover, wine as well as any kind of drinks, if you drink with a large amount, will fill the bladder and cause the phenomenon of nocturia. As a result, this activity will adversely have negative effects on the quality of pregnant women’s sleep.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/pregnant-women-should-avoid-wine-or-alcohol.jpg" alt="Pregnant women should avoid wine or alcohol" width="490" height="406" /></div>\r\n<div><em>Pregnant women should avoid wine or alcohol</em><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>5. Avoid severe activities before bed.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>It is essential to avoid some exercises or exercises with intensive degree and requiring more energy during pregnant period, especially before bed time. Instead, they can relax muscles and do some gentle agitation by walking after lunch, which is the most suitable choice.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/pregnant-avoid-severe-activities.jpg" alt="Pregnant avoid severe activities" width="500" height="284" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>6. Drink a glass of milk before bed</strong></h3>\r\n<div>According to several studies, drink a glass of warm milk before 30- minute to a hour bed will increase the quality of the pregnant women’s sleep. They should maintain this habit to have a deep sleep, supplying nutrition for their body but also their fetus.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/drink-a-glass-of-milk-before-bed.jpg" alt="Drink a glass of milk before bed" width="500" height="333" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>7. Balance the psychology.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Women should not keep themselves anxious or nervous all the time during pregnant period because this will lead to insomnia. Moreover, psychological conflict that women encounter during pregnancy to after giving birth is the origin of psychological disorder in their baby born.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/balance-the-psychology.jpg" alt="Balance the psychology with pregnant women" width="500" height="331" />&#160;<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Recent research has shown that the quality of relationship between a mom and a baby during pregnancy have significant impact on the information of your baby. If you are usually angry, unhappy during this time, your baby born will be always in the mood of sorrow and easily losing anger with others. Therefore, pregnant women should keep themselves relaxed and comfortable all the time.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>8. Gentle massage</strong></h3>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>Gentle massage plays an important role in reducing the level of muscle tension, relaxing muscles and their mind. Therefore, it is absolutely essential for pregnant women’s health if they have mild message before bed and as a result of having a deep sleep.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/gentle-massage-pregnant-women.jpg" alt="Gentle massage pregnant women" width="369" height="553" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>9. Imagine for a moment before bed</strong></h3>\r\nRelax your mind and imagine a little of what you like or wish such as you are playing with your baby born happily to get relaxation, as a result, you can fall asleep easily.<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/Imagine-for-a-moment-before-bed.jpg" alt="Imagine for a moment before bed" width="500" height="282" />\r\n<p class="MsoNormal"><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>10. Select proper sleeping position.</strong></h3>\r\nDepending on the stage of pregnancy, health condition and personal preference, pregnant women can choose the most appropriate sleeping posture whether the doctor recommend that laying on the right may help reduce pressure on the abdomen, leading them to feel more comfortable and easily falling asleep. Some pregnant mothers also prefer placing a pillow under their back to have comfortable sleeping posture.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/select-proper-sleeping-position.jpg" alt="Select proper sleeping position" width="500" height="307" /><br />\r\n&#160;</div>', '', 'pregnant-women-sleeping.jpg', '', NULL, 'Pregnant women, Pregnant women''s sleeping', 'Pregnant women often face the problems of insomnia. Here are some tips for any women in the period of pregnancy to improve the quality of sleeping to avoid and have a good health for them and their baby.', '2016-01-29 08:39:52', 0, 78, 3, 1),
(32, 'How to draw a soccer ball', 'how-to-draw-a-soccer-ball', 'Emily', '', 'Soccer is a game loved by almost the entire world but the fact is that the game is called football in all other countries except Canada and US', '<p class="MsoNormal">Soccer is a game loved by almost the entire world but the fact is that the game is called football in all other countries except Canada and US. The game is almost similar to rugby with only a little difference that in Soccer you are not allowed to touch the ball with hands like in rugby. Want to draw your very own soccer ball, we can do it now with this <b>drawing for kids</b> lesson, I said it for real, guys!<br />\n<br />\n<br />\n<o:p></o:p></p>', '<strong><span new="">STEP 1 :</span></strong><span new=""><br />\nThe soccer ball is all about geometry. So, we start with one hexagon in the center of a paper. Perfect like a beehive’s structure, and not just your basic six-sided hexagon. They like "perfect" hexagons, meaning all six sides are of equal length. They go for the jewelers'' version — precise, just so. Every cell in the honeycomb is a hexagon - what a great example of <b><a href="http://kidsidea.net/kid-kids-art/drawing-for-kids.html">drawing for kids</a></b> combines science for kids, huh?<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-soccer-ball-step1.jpg" alt="How to draw a soccer ball" width="500" height="216" /><br />\n<strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 2 :<br />\n</span></strong><span new=""> Add a pentagon with one line common in both. Now, we are playing puzzles here, put another shape onto the right place to form a good structure for our soccer ball.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-soccer-ball-step2.jpg" alt="How to draw a soccer ball step 2" width="500" height="222" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 3 : </strong><br />\nContinue with one more pentagon on another line, a Mickey’s head, do you think so?&#160; Do you ever consider the relationship between your age and your soccer ball size, here you should know: “Players who are 5 to 8 years old play with a size three soccer ball. Youth soccer, ages 4 to 12, play with a size four, and anyone 13 and over plays with a size five.”<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-soccer-ball-step3.jpg" alt="How to draw a soccer ball step 3" width="500" height="222" /><br />\n<strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 4: </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nDraw one more pentagon below, oh, look at it. It likes a poison mask now, or a bull head. Quite an impressive symbol, right guys?<br />\n</span><br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-soccer-ball-step4.jpg" alt="How to draw a soccer ball step 4" width="500" height="247" /><br />\n<span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 5 :</strong> <br />\nWhat we want to do next is draw the round shape of the Soccer ball using the small shape of a rhombus. Do you know “the oldest football in existence is 450 years old, made from deer skin and containing a pig’s bladder? &#160;It was once the property of Mary Queen of Scots and is now displayed in Scotland’s Stirling Smith Museum.”<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-soccer-ball-step5.jpg" alt="How to draw a soccer ball step 5" width="500" height="288" /><br />\n<strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 6 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nAttach the lines and make more hexagons and pentagons. You guys can use rules here for perfection the lines, ask help if needed, but trust me, you are doing amazing!<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-soccer-ball-step6.jpg" alt="How to draw a soccer ball step 6" width="500" height="279" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 7 : </strong><br />\nComplete the ball by drawing the outer circle, with the help of circle drawing tool - compa, maybe. Now, you have gone a long way, we’re about to see our result right in the next step.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-soccer-ball-step7.jpg" alt="How to draw a soccer ball step 7" width="500" height="277" /><br />\n</span><strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 8 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nTo make it become reality, color a soccer ball with shades of white and black. Your friend should in “oh” for that drawing you just made.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-soccer-ball-final-step.jpg" width="500" height="280" alt="" /><br />\n</span>\n<p class="MsoNormal">Can you imagine how beautiful this will look on the board in your room or in your book! <o:p></o:p></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal">Just let you know more: The Soccer World Cup is the biggest tournament around the world. It''s held once in four years and a large amount of people watches it around the world. In one game of Soccer, every player runs about 6 miles on an average. The game was believed to have originated in China even when it is the most popular game in European countries.<o:p></o:p></p>\n<span new="">Having fun, stay tuned for the next <b>art kids</b> tutorial right here. See you!</span> </span></span></span>', '', 'draw-soccer-ball.jpg', '', NULL, 'How to draw a soccer ball, Activities for kids', 'If you too are a Soccer fan and would like to draw a Soccer ball for your pin board, so you’re in the right place. Let’s start with collecting pen/paper/pencil/paintbrush and get started. Our art activities for kids tutorial here to help you make the task easier than ever', '2014-10-22 03:08:49', 55, 45, 9, 106),
(33, 'How to draw a kite step by step', 'how-to-draw-a-kite-step-by-step', 'Emily', '', 'Kite flying is an interesting hobby! Once started, it becomes almost an addiction for young kids', '<span>Kite flying is an interesting hobby! Once started, it becomes almost an addiction for young kids. They feel excited as they see their kite go higher and higher in the sky. If you cannot fly a kite but would like to do so, you can at least try and draw them on paper first to get connected to them in some way. So if you would like to draw a kite, follow this <b><a href="http://kidsidea.net/kid-kids-art/drawing-for-kids.html">drawing for kids</a></b> step by step lesson to draw a beautiful kite flying high in the sky<br />\n<br type="_moz" />\n</span>', '<strong><span>STEP 1 : </span></strong><span><br />\nDo you kids know a fact that: ”</span><span>A kite is an aircraft consisting of multiple wings tethered to an anchor system”. A kite flying in the sky looks like a diamond floating&#160;</span><span>So to make the typical diamond shape for our kite, let’s <span>start with the top triangular lines of the kite</span>, just like a roof – top of a house, right?<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-kite-step1.jpg" alt="How to draw a kite step 1" width="500" height="170" /><br />\n<p class="Normal1"><strong>STEP 2 :<span> </span></strong><span><br />\nFirst step’s done; now we want to complete the diamond shape of the kite with the inverted triangle.</span><span> In fact, this diamond frame is often made by resilient bamboo for a strong, lightweight framework. That’s why in Asia countries, we make kites more than Europe countries because materials ideal for kite building are readily available.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-kite-step2.jpg" alt="How to draw a kite step 2" width="500" height="239" /><br />\n</span><span><br />\n<strong>STEP 3 :</strong> <br />\nThen, we’re going to draw the lines joining all the points</span><span>. This move makes our kites stronger and a firm structure. A mind-blowing fact more to know for kids: “Humans are sometimes bound to a large kite to fly. The first known example is Yuan Huangtou in 550 CE.” Wow! One day, maybe you guys can build a Giant Kite, which can carry you fly above the sky, who knows.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-kite-step3.jpg" alt="How to draw a kite step 3" width="500" height="234" /><br />\n</span><span><br />\n<strong>STEP 4 : </strong><br />\nAlright, how are you doing? Good. Next, we want to draw the string attached to the lower point of the kite.</span><span> In reality, this flying line is made of fine, high-tensile-strength silk for the <strong>finest kites</strong>.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-kite-step4.jpg" alt="How to draw a kite step 4" width="500" height="272" /><br />\n</span><span><br />\n<strong>STEP 5 :</strong> <br />\nNow, we want to decorate our kite, we need to add some patterns, so I choose to draw a series of bows on the string of the kite</span><span>, you guys can do your own version, draw anything you want, maybe circle, squirrel, stars, moon, or even a cat&#160;</span><span><b><a href="http://kidsidea.net/kid-kids-art/painting-for-kids.html">Painting for kids</a></b> is all about freedom to create yourself.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-kite-step5.jpg" alt="How to draw a kite step 5" width="500" height="284" /><br />\n</span><span><br />\n<strong>STEP 6 : </strong><br />\nTo make the kite look real, we’re gonna draw triangles in all the areas of the kite.</span><span> It’s an <b>art for kids</b> tip, you guys should write down in your note book! Awesome!<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-kite-step6.jpg" alt="How to draw a kite step 6" width="500" height="282" /><br />\n</span><span><o:p></o:p></span><span><span><br />\n<strong>Step 7 : </strong><br />\nNow, we need to fully control our kite, so what we’re gonna do next is to draw the strings to all points which will help the kite to fly. </span><span>Like this, go on, you guys are doing fantastic.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-kite-step7.jpg" alt="How to draw a kite step 7" width="500" height="270" /><br />\n</span><span><br />\n<strong>STEP 8 :</strong> <br />\nFinally, we come to the funniest part: Coloring!!! So, I pick three basic colors, all of them are bright colors: Red, yellow and blue</span><span>; to make the kite stand out. You can do it just you </span><span>Make it colorful and alive.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/draw-kite-final-step.jpg" width="500" height="265" alt="" /><br />\n</span></span></p>\n<p class="Normal1">The kite really looks beautiful and I would really like to fly one in the sky. For more objects, please <span>keep reading our <b><a href="http://kidsidea.net/kids-art.html">art for kids</a>’ </b>article on the website: kidsidea.net.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\n<p class="Normal1">Maybe you don’t know: “<span>A Japanese kite maker has the world record of flying the largest number of kites at one time. The kite flying game was banned in Japan at one time because people used to prefer them instead of working. It was thanks to the concept of kite that the idea of the airplane was developed”.</span></p>\n<p class="Normal1"><span>        <span><br />\nSee you all next time, bye!</span></span></p>\n</span>', '', 'draw-kite.jpg', '', NULL, 'How to draw a kite, Activities for kids, Art for kids', 'Kites may be flown for recreation, art or other practical uses. Sport kites can be flown in aerial ballet, sometimes as part of a competition. There are so many interesting things we want to experience with the amazing KITE, so why not draw for ourselves a kite right now; these art activities for kids will definitely help!', '2014-10-22 04:04:59', 55, 45, 9, 106),
(34, 'How to draw a fairy step by step', 'how-to-draw-a-fairy-step-by-step', 'Emily', '', 'Fairies are among the most popular magical characters for young girls who get attracted to their beauty and sparkle', '<span new="">Fairies are among the most popular magical characters for young girls who get attracted to their beauty and sparkle. Fairies are dreamlike characters that come is all sizes, fly with delicate wings and have the power to create magic. If you too would like to draw them just follow the <b>painting for kids’</b> step by step lesson and you can become an artist in no time.</span>', '<strong><span new="">STEP 1 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nBefore we start, I just want to make a quick notice for you guys: This lesson is not easy, but don’t you worry, it’s far from simple but never close to the hard one. All you need just a certain amount of time and patience, we’re right here with you. So let’s get started with the wavy hair of the fairy. Do you know by chances that: “Tangles in your hair – sometimes known as elf locks – are the work of fairies”. Draw some curve lines; try to smooth down the hair, to make your fairy look beautiful, if you never draw girl’s hair before; ask your parents give you a helping hand!<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-fairy-step1.jpg" alt="How to draw a fairy step 1" width="500" height="276" /><br />\n<strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 2 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nThe, what we want to do now is to draw the beautiful face with eyes and a lovely smile. These details need times, guys, so be patient, and you can do it. </span><span new="">J</span><span new=""> One thing I just recently knew: “Children – particularly young girls – are most likely to see these little people.” So hey young little girls, have you seen them?<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-fairy-step2.jpg" alt="How to draw a fairy step 2" width="500" height="241" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 3 : </strong><br />\nNow, it’s becoming a little bit harder when we will draw one hand with fingers as if pointing at something. Do it slowly, carefully, I am sure you guys are doing good at it. Sometimes, we need to raise the bar of our<b> <a href="http://kidsidea.net/kids-art.html">art activities for kids</a>, </b>when you do something more complicated like this fairy, you can improve your drawing skill.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-fairy-step3.jpg" alt="How to draw a fairy step 3" width="500" height="230" /><br />\n</span><strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 4 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nOnce you can draw one hand of your fairy, there is no way you can’t do the rest. Let’s draw another hand with fingers fully spread out. Seem like your fairy is opening her arms to give you a big hug, maybe, right?<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-fairy-step4.jpg" alt="How to draw a fairy step 4" width="500" height="231" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 5 : </strong><br />\nFairies love to dance!! So you girls definitely want to draw a gorgeous dress for your stunning fairy! We are doing it now in this step. So, we will draw the flared dress and the wand they carry to create magic around them. Some kids asked me: “How do I tell that a fairy is coming?” My answer to that question is: “The disappearance of small objects can be a clue they have been visiting”. So, watch out, girls, a ripple in the water or sudden chill often indicates their presence.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-fairy-step5.jpg" alt="How to draw a fairy step 5" width="500" height="282" /><br />\n</span><strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 6 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nAbsolutely I think what makes a fairy so attractive to young girls beside her beauty is the ability to fly. So we’re gonna draw the legs in a flying position.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-fairy-step6.jpg" alt="How to draw a fairy step 6" width="500" height="280" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 7 : </strong><br />\nNow it’s time for the delicate wings that they fly around with, you guys can’t miss it! Wow, she is so close, sweet heart.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-fairy-step7.jpg" alt="How to draw a fairy step 7" width="500" height="278" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 8 : </strong><br />\nWho wants to color a fairy??? I can hear you scream: Me, me, me <img src="http://kidsidea.net/fckeditor/editor/images/smiley/msn/regular_smile.gif" alt="" /></span><span new="">So, what’re you waiting for? Color the fairy of any color of your choice. I am doing the blue one, fabulous!<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-fairy-final-step.jpg" alt="How to draw a fairy final step" width="500" height="275" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\nAlways remember to color the wings of a fairy in a similar color as their dress. If you want to know more about fairies, here what you should read :<br />\n</span>\n<p class="MsoNormal" are="" fond="" of="" fresh="" mushrooms="" and="" green="" forests.="" they="" get="" attracted="" by="" laughter="" fun.="" live=""  islands="" or="" in="" hollow="" trees="" their="" presence="" can="" be="" felt="" a="" ripple="" the="" water="" shower="" sparkling="" glitter.="" love="" music="" to="" dance.="" have="" an="" ability="" make="" themselves="" visible="" invisible="" according="" mood.="" several="" hundred="" years="" old.="" like="" nectar="" just="">&#160;</p>\n<span new=""><span \nfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\nmso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">“Fairies are fond of fresh flowers, mushrooms and green forests. They get attracted by laughter and fun. They live on islands or in hollow trees and their presence can be felt by a ripple in the water or a shower of sparkling glitter. They love music and love to dance. They have an ability to make themselves visible or invisible according to their mood. They live to be several hundred years old. They like honey, milk, and nectar – just like you, girls!”<br />\n</span><br />\nFor more objects, you can click on the <b><a href="http://kidsidea.net/kids-art.html">arts for kids</a>’</b> menu on our website and, like magic, you will learn to draw! <br />\n<br />\nHave fun while drawing and we see you next time</span></span>', '', 'how-to-draw-fairy.jpg', '', NULL, 'How to draw a fairy, How to draw anime', 'Fairies size ranges, from tiny fairies smaller than fireflies to powerful forces that guide the wind. Don’t you be fascinated about those little sparkle fairies? Imagine how great it could feel if you girls got one for your own, so we’re gonna do it right now in our drawing for kids tutorial, How to draw a fairy! ', '2014-10-22 04:47:09', 52, 45, 9, 106),
(35, 'How to draw an alien step by step', 'how-to-draw-an-alien-step-by-step', 'Emily', '', 'It is true that kids like to live in their own land of dreams and love to make objects out of nothing. Aliens and unidentified flying objects or UFO''s definitely fit this category! ', '<span new="">It is true that kids like to live in their own land of dreams and love to make objects out of nothing. Aliens and unidentified flying objects or UFO''s definitely fit this category! Although there is no particular form of these Aliens as nobody has seen them, here in our <a href="http://kidsidea.net/kid-kids-art/drawing-for-kids.html">drawing for kids</a>’ step by step lesson we have tried to give your imagination a shape. Let’s gather our pen/paper/pencil/paintbrush and start drawing these Aliens</span>', '<strong><span new="">STEP 1 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nLike a typical shape of the head, we will start with the face in the shape of an oval. An egg-shape face for our alien, maybe we don’t know exactly how it goes, but we’re gonna draw a cute alien for sure, guys </span><span new="">Do you know what does “UFO” stand for? It stands for “Unidentified flying object”. UFO is any aerial phenomenon whose cause cannot be easily or immediately identified by the observer.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-alien-step1.jpg" alt="How to draw an alien step 1" width="500" height="218" /><br />\n<strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 2 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nAlien equals strangeness and bizarreness, so next thing up, we want to imagine the ears and draw it! Here I will draw two triangular shaped curved ears on either side, just like an elf in old fairy story. Wow, how great it is, kids; we can create all the parts of our alien, from tip to toe, the beauty of <b><a href="http://kidsidea.net/kids-art.html">art activities for kids</a></b> is right here, be free.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-alien-step2.jpg" alt="How to draw an alien step 2" width="500" height="211" /><br />\n</span><strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 3 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nNow, we suppose that alien need to contact with each other by some signals, so next thing we want to do is draw two antennae on the head instead of hair. So cute! Look like twin little mushrooms on a candy, do you guys think so?<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-alien-step3.jpg" alt="How to draw an alien step 3" width="500" height="198" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 4 : </strong><br />\nOur alien is a nice, sweet alien so he needs a big smile! We’re gonna do it right now. Draw a smile and then two small ovals at the neck. Oh, the more strange drawing you got, the more exciting our alien is gonna be.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-alien-step4.jpg" alt="How to draw an alien step 4" width="500" height="213" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 5 : </strong><br />\nTo be a little bit robot-holic, I want to draw hands in the shape of a claw. Do you know that back in 2004, 3 independent groups all reported massively high amounts of methane within the atmosphere of Mars? That''s not very exciting. Until, that is, you realize that nearly all methane on earth is created by living organisms. Are they really out there?<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-alien-step5.jpg" alt="How to draw an alien step 5" width="500" height="249" /><br />\n</span><span new=""><br />\n<strong>STEP 6 : </strong><br />\nNow, you do just it, draw the body and legs and complete the Alien of your dream. This art for kids tutorials is not just fun, it is aimed to give you kids cool fact about the object. For an alien as an object, we have some more to tell you: “Our galaxy, the Milky Way galaxy, measures up to 120,000 light-years across and contains about 400 billion stars. It’s said that about half of these stars include at least one planet within their orbit. That''s a lot of planets, and a good chance for alien life we haven''t yet discovered.”<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-alien-step6.jpg" alt="How to draw an alien step 6" width="500" height="270" /><br />\n</span><strong><span new=""><br />\nSTEP 7 : </span></strong><span new=""><br />\nAlright, finally get to the last point, draw concentric circles for yes and you are ready to color the Alien now. These hypnotized eyes are really out of this world, don’t you agree?<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-alien-step7.jpg" alt="How to draw an alien step 7" width="500" height="269" /><br />\n</span>\n<p class="MsoNormal" strong=""><br />\nAlthough we are not sure what color they are, let your imagination go and color them whatever color you like. I like green, the leaf’s color, it means living thing. Hope one day; we can meet a real alien.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-alien-final.jpg" alt="Final step" width="500" height="278" /></p>\n<p class="MsoNormal">&#160;</p>\nDoesn''t it look cute! We like to believe that Aliens, if there are any such things in the world, are not dangerous beings. <o:p></o:p>\n<p>&#160;</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" there="" is="" no="" proof="" but=""  an="" average="" around="" sightings="" of="" watching="" alien="" have="" been="" reported="" the="" world.="" another="" fact="" that="" remains="" to="" has="" ever="" tracked="" atmosphere.="" americans="" are="" more="" prone="" existence="" as="" compared="" other="" countries.="">&#160;</p>\n<p class="MsoNormal" it="" look="" we="" like="" to="" believe="" that="" if="" there="" are="" any="" such="" things="" in="" the="" not="" dangerous="" beings.=""><span \nfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\nmso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">Although there is no proof but on an average around 192 sightings of watching an Alien have been reported around the world. Another fact that remains is that, to date, no Alien has ever been tracked around the earth''s atmosphere. Americans are more prone to Alien existence as compared to other countries<br />\n<br />\n</span><span \nfont-family:"Calibri","sans-serif";mso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-fareast-font-family:\nCalibri;mso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;mso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\nmso-bidi-font-family:"Times New Roman";mso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;\nmso-ansi-language:EN-US;mso-fareast-language:EN-US;mso-bidi-language:AR-SA">For other objects you can keep reading on the step by step <b>art for kids</b>’ lessons right here, at our website and enjoy drawing them.</span></p>\n</span>', '', 'how-to-draw-alien.jpg', '', NULL, 'How to draw an alien', 'Do you believe in alien? Are we not alone in this universe? It’s hard to tell, but alien and UFO have always been something super special, which can make us go beyond our mind, especially to kids, who dream and have strong belief in things that adults don’t So, why not drawing a alien – made by you, wow, this is gonna be cool! This painting for kids is here to help!', '2014-10-22 05:16:20', 52, 41, 9, 106),
(36, 'How to draw a rose step by step', 'how-to-draw-a-rose-step-by-step', 'Emily', '', 'Roses are one of the favorite flowers of people all over the world', 'Roses are one of the favorite flowers of people all over the world. Almost 85% Americans have voted them as their favorite flowers. If you want to draw them on paper and then sing the rhyme that goes "Roses are red, violets are blue" then lets follow the <strong>drawing for kids</strong>’ step by step lesson and become an artist. Collect your pen/paper/paintbrush/pencil and start drawing a beautiful rose', '<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-step1.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose step 1" width="500" height="277" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>STEP 1 : </strong><br />\nDon’t you guys know each color rose has its own special significance. We’re gonna draw the rose from the inside all the way out. So, first thing to do is start with the small petals inside a rose that make them beautiful. A tiny spiral line right in the middle is a good start, guys.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-step2.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose step 2" width="500" height="312" /><br />\n<strong><br />\nSTEP 2 : </strong><br />\nNow, what we want to do is to start from one point draw more petals around the inner portion. These petals look like almost oval shapes, spin around the middle, such an easy way to do art activities for kids. You are gonna be blown away by that stunning queen of flowers. Coveted through the ages for its simply beauty and intoxicating fragrance, there’s no better way to send a heartfelt message than with the classic rose, you guys should know that!<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-step3.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose step 3" width="500" height="306" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>STEP 3 : </strong><br />\nWhen drawing a rose, it’s all about elegant and refined lines. You kids can do it with a little of patience, kindness and carefulness. I am sure you are doing just fine. So, we want to draw concentric petals on both sides now.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-step4.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose step 4" width="500" height="302" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>STEP 4 : </strong><strong><br />\n</strong>Keep going by drawing a bigger petal folded outwards. We would like to share a interesting fact about rose right here: “Long associated with beauty and perfection, red roses are a time-honored way to say “I love you.” Whether it’s for a birthday, Valentine’s Day or just to express appreciation on any old day, there’s no better way than a bouquet of red roses to express your feelings.” So, you guys know how to show the love, right?<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-step5.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose step 5" width="500" height="294" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>STEP 5 : </strong><br />\nNow, the only thing we should do is adding more petals, on the left first and then on the right. I am left- handed so for me, I will draw two petals on the left.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-step6.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose step 6" width="500" height="298" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>Step 6 :</strong> <br />\nThen, I draw the balance on right with more petals. Our roses must look well-proportioned.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-step7.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose step 7" width="500" height="302" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>STEP 7 : </strong><br />\nNow, it’s time to add some green to brighten our rose. I mean we will complete the rose with a stem and a few leaves&#160;<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-step8.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose step 8" width="500" height="301" /><br />\n<br />\n<strong>STEP 8 : </strong><br />\nAnd we’re done. We have used the most common color, red to color our rose. You can use any color of your choice. We want to say: “WE LOVE YOU”.<br />\n<br />\n<img src="http://kidsidea.net/uploaded/kidart/how-to-draw-rose-final.jpg" alt="How to draw a rose final step" width="500" height="279" /><br />\n<div><br />\nFor more objects you can keep visit our website to get more <strong>art for kids</strong>’ step by step lessons and articles and enjoy.&#160;</div>\n<div><br />\nDid you know there are more than 15000 varieties of roses that are available around the world? If we believe mythology, it is believed that the thorns on the roses grew when Cupid accidently the shot an arrow in the garden of roses. A hips of the rose posses a large amount of vitamin C even more than all fruits and vegetables. You can get a rose named after you but with a high price of $15000. I don''t think it''s worth it though!</div>', '', 'how-to-draw-rose.jpg', '', NULL, 'How to draw a rose, Art activies for kids', 'As one of the most enduring symbols for love and appreciation, it’s no surprise that roses are among the most admired and evocative of flowers. If your mother’s birthday or special day is coming, and you guys want to give them a sign of your love, why not drawing a gorgous rose by following this easy painting for kids’ tutorial, and gift her that adorable flower, it’s gonna be so cool', '2014-10-22 11:16:13', 54, 41, 9, 106),
(53, 'Causes of sore throat and hoarse voice', 'causes-of-sore-throat-and-hoarse-voice', 'Don Miller', '', 'Sore throat (pharyngitis) is the condition of mycodermatitis and almost drives the patient irritated', '&#160;', '<h3><strong>I. What is sore throat?</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Sore throat-the main symptom of pharyngitis is pain or irritation of the throat which is even worse when you swallow.&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Sore throat is the symptom of many different diseases but the most common cause is colds or flu. Sore throat caused by a virus is often improved with home care while strep throat, less common type of throat caused by bacteria needs to be treated by antibiotics. &#160;Most cases of sore throat have not caused serious complications. But some severe cases of sore throat can result in heart, kidney and joints diseases.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<h3><strong>II. Causes of sore throat</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Our throat is so sensitive and easy to get infections. Patients at any age, especially young children, the elderly and person with weak resistance, workers or people who work in air-conditioned environment for a long time often have sore throat. Although this is a common disease, not everyone knows the causes of sore throat. There are some typical causes listed below:</div>\r\n<u><br />\r\n</u>\r\n<div>1. &#160;<u>Virus infection</u></div>\r\n<div>The disease causing sore throat includes:</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Colds</li>\r\n    <li>Flu</li>\r\n    <li>Mononucleosis (mono).</li>\r\n    <li>Chickenpox&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Measles.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><br />\r\n2. &#160;<u>Bacterial infections</u></div>\r\n<div>Bacterial infections can cause sore throat, including:</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Strep throat is caused by a bacterium called Streptococcus pyogenes, or Group A streptococcus.</li>\r\n    <li>Pertussis which is easily infectious through respiration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<div>3. &#160;<u>Other causes of sore throat including</u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Allergies: Allergy to mold, pet dander, pollen and dust can cause a sore throat. The problem can become more complicated by postnasal drip which can may stimulate and lead to pharyngitis.&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Muscle strain. Yelling at a sporting event, trying to talk to someone in a noisy environment or talk for long periods without a break can lead to a sore throat and hoarseness.</li>\r\n    <li>Gastroesophageal reflux disease (GERD)- a digestive disorder where stomach acid or other fluids of the stomach back in the esophagus. Other symptoms can consist of &#160;heartburn, hoarseness, vomiting and gastric sensation of a lump in the throat.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<div>4. &#160;<u>Environment factors</u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Contaminants : polluted air inside or outside can cause pharyngitis. These may include: dust, smoke, pet dander, pollen, mold..</li>\r\n    <li>Climate or weather in which it is too hot or too cold. Especially, when sleeping, we often forget to keep our body warm, put the fan or air-conditioner direct to ourselves.</li>\r\n    <li>Food hygiene problem: kind of food, unhygienic drinks which contain so many bacteria also can cause pharyngitis.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<div>5. &#160;<u>Personal factor</u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Personal hygiene: The activity of brushing the teeth improperly and unregularly can drive harmful bacteria staying in the oral cavity, which results in ease inflammation.</li>\r\n    <li>Alcoholic beverages, spicy foods, fried foods such fried, baked food: Food that is too spicy or contains alcohol can cause sore throat&#160;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/brush-your-teeth.jpg" alt="Brush your teeth regularly and properly" width="500" height="335" /><br />\r\n<span><em>Brush your teeth regularly and properly</em></span><br />\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong><br />\r\nIII. Symptoms of Sore throat</strong></h3>\r\n<div>The symptoms of sore throat depend on the different cause factor. We can indicate some main symptoms as below:</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Trouble in swallowing</li>\r\n    <li>Chills&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Worse sore throat when swallowing or talking</li>\r\n    <li>Scratchy or pain sensation in the throat</li>\r\n    <li>Dry throat</li>\r\n    <li>Pain or swollen glands in the neck or jaw</li>\r\n    <li>Swollen, red tonsils</li>\r\n    <li>Hoarse or muffled voice</li>\r\n    <li>Refusing to eat ( in children)</li>\r\n    <li>White patches or pus on the tonsils.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\nThat common infection can cause sore throat can lead to signs and symptoms including:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Have a fever</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Runny nose</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Sneeze</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Body aches</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Headache&#160;</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Nausea or vomiting</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\nTake the children to the doctor if your child faces some of these severe symptoms:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Difficulty breathing</li>\r\n    <li>Abnormal drooling, which may indicate the inability to swallow</li>\r\n    <li>Difficult swallowing</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\nAdults should go to see the doctor when facing following problems related to sore throat such as:<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Severe throat pain which can last more than a week</li>\r\n    <li>Difficult breathing and swallowing</li>\r\n    <li>Have a fever over 101F</li>\r\n    <li>Difficulty in opening mouth</li>\r\n    <li>Athritis</li>\r\n    <li>Earache</li>\r\n    <li>Blood in saliva or phlegm</li>\r\n    <li>Constantly recurring sore throat.</li>\r\n    <li>A tumor in the neck.</li>\r\n    <li>Hoarseness that lasts more than two weeks.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>IV. Treatments</strong><span><br />\r\n</span></h3>\r\n<p><u><span>1. </span>Drugs.</u></p>\r\n<div>If the symptoms of pharyngitis which is caused by viral infections lasts from 5 to 7 days, patients do not need medical treatments.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>-&#160;Infectious treatment:</div>\r\n<div>The doctor will prescribe antibiotics. Patients can take penicillin which is the most commonly prescribed for infections such as strep throat for 10 days. If allergic to penicillin, the doctor will prescribe alternative antibiotics.</div>\r\n<div>Patients have to obey the full procedure of treatment even if symptoms disappear completely. Failure to take all the medicine as directed can drive more severe infections or spread to other parts of the body. Do not use the full range of antibiotics which can treat sore throats, especially, increases the risk for rheumatic fever and severe nephritis.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<div><u>2. Lifestyle and home remedies.<strong><br type="_moz" />\r\n</strong></u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Rest: have a plenty of sleep and rest your voice</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Water: Drink plenty of water to prevent dehydration and moisturize the throat.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">The foods and beverages. Use warm water, coffee, tea or hot water with honey which can soothe a sore throat.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Gargle salt water. Gargle salt - 1 teaspoon (5 ml) salt with 237 ml of warm water may help soothe a sore throat. Rinse mouth and then spit it out.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Air humidity. Use a cool air humidifier to eliminate dry air can irritate a sore throat or sit a few minutes in a wet bathroom.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Avoid stimulants. Keep avoiding cigarette smoke and cleaning products can irritate the throat.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\nTreatment of pain and fever. Ibuprofen (Advil, Motrin, others) or acetaminophen (Tylenol, others) may reduce the pain throat. Aspirin has been linked with Reye''s syndrome, so be careful when using aspirin to children or teenagers. Although aspirin is approved for use in children over 2 years of age, children and teenagers recovering from chickenpox or flu-like symptoms should never take aspirin.<br type="_moz" />\r\n<br />\r\n<div><u>3. Alternative medicine</u></div>\r\n<div>Besides some typical medicine such as antibiotics, we can use herbal or alternative products for sore throat like packed tea, sprays or lozenges. Here are some recommend below:</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Slippery elm.</li>\r\n    <li>Silkworm enzyme.</li>\r\n    <li>Andrographis.</li>\r\n    <li>Licorice root.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><u>4.&#160;Prevention</u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Wash your hands thoroughly and frequently after sneezing or coughing and before eating, after using the toilet.</li>\r\n    <li>Avoid sharing food, cups or utensils.</li>\r\n    <li>Avoid touching public phones</li>\r\n    <li>Cough or sneeze into a tissue and throw it away.</li>\r\n    <li>Avoid close contact with sick people.</li>\r\n    <li>Humidify your home if the air is dry</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br type="_moz" />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', 'sore-throat-symptoms.jpg', '', NULL, 'Sore throat treatment', 'Sore throat (pharyngitis) is the condition of mycodermatitis and almost drives the patient irritated', '2016-01-29 06:32:14', 0, 84, 6, 1);
INSERT INTO `tbl_posts` (`post_id`, `post_title`, `post_title_rewrite`, `post_author`, `post_source`, `post_shotinfo`, `post_info`, `post_value`, `post_tags`, `post_image`, `post_picture`, `post_status`, `post_keys`, `post_des`, `post_date`, `type_id`, `cago_id`, `cate_id`, `user_id`) VALUES
(42, 'Digestive disorders in children', 'digestive-disorders-in-children', 'Don Miller', '', 'What is digestive disorders', 'Digestive disorder (Gastroinstestinal problems) is a term often used to refer to abnormal function of stomach. When your child encounters typical signs such as bloating, indigestion, heartburn, constipation, diarrhea or malabsorption', '<h3><strong>I. What is digestive disorders</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Digestive disorder (Gastroinstestinal problems) is a term often used to refer to abnormal function of stomach. When your child encounters typical signs such as bloating, indigestion, heartburn, constipation, diarrhea or malabsorption.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<h3><strong>II. Cause of digestive disorder</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Children with immature and incomplete digestive or limited immune system often suffer from digestive disorders with typical symptoms such as flatulence, tympanous, constipation, diarrhea or malabsorption, which has negative impacts on the child’s heath, the ability to absorb nutrients and the development of the child in his early years. Therefore, understanding 5 main causes of digestive disorders in children will help parents have intensive knowledge of this disease to prevent and prepare better healthcare.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>1. &#160;<u>Weak immune system.</u></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\nWhile the period of being in the womb, babies can live in a sterile environment, especially they are shield and encircled carefully, but when babies are born, they are exposed to the real world, new life in which their immune systems are so immature that bacteria can easily penetrate and causes other diseases, not only digestive disorders. Equally important, the rate of newly born babies suffering from digestive disorders is incredible high if their mother cannot give the babies the first drop of the breast.&#160;<br />\r\n<u><br />\r\n</u>\r\n<div><u><br />\r\n</u>2. &#160;<u><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Antibiotics.</span></u></div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>That the children take antibiotics to treat some diseases also cause digestive disorders because during this time, their immune systems is so weak and incomplete, antibiotics which are taken into their body not only kill harmful but also beneficial bacteria. This activity results in typical symptoms of digestive disorders such as diarrhea, constipation which is very dangerous to their health. That if this symptoms lasts for so long will cause chronic colitics, digestive disorder, leading to malnutrition, immune deficiency in children.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\nTherefore, before and during pregnancy period, any mom should fully inject vaccination and babies also should be injected vaccination right after they were born to avoid maximum antibiotics when they are too small. In case of babies’ taking medicine, parents should adhere strictly to the guidance of doctors to avoid digestive disorders.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/Inject-vaccine-to-prevent-digestive-disorders.jpg" alt="Inject vaccine to prevent digestive disorders" width="500" height="293" /><br />\r\n<span><em>Inject vaccine to prevent digestive disorders</em></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div><u><br />\r\n</u>3. &#160;<u><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Unreasonable diets.</span></u></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\nNutrition for young children plays an important role in protecting health, improving resistance, preventing diseases and providing a foundation for a comprehensive youth development. However, it’s the limit of children’s resistance, the beneficial bacteria in digestive system works less efficiently if diets is not appreciate and unsafe due to infection, poison or food ingredients which are not consistent with the child’s age, which will cause digestive disorders.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Moreover, when bacteria attacks, if natural disposition and the intestinal wall of the children is too weak leading to the disease more severe, especially in the case of serious food poisoning which results in the child’s constant diarrhea, vomiting and abdominal cramps…If this condition is not treated in time, his lives will be in danger.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<div><br />\r\n4. &#160;<u>Negative psychological condition</u></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\nWhen the child encounters pressure, anxiety, stress, restlessness…, it also commonly causes digestive disorders because at this time, the child’s digestion is not favorable. The enzyme secretion needs to break down and food intake reduces quite significantly. Therefore, that the children is in comfortable, relaxed and happy mood will drive the child to prevent digestive disorders, improve nutrient absorption and to develop more comprehensively.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/negative-psychological-condition-in-children.jpg" alt=" When the child encounters pressure, anxiety, stress, restlessness…, it also commonly causes digestive disorders" width="500" height="336" /><br />\r\n<div><span><em>When the child encounters pressure, anxiety, stress, restlessness…, it also commonly causes digestive disorders</em></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div><br />\r\n5. <u>Unsanitary living environment</u><u><br />\r\n<br type="_moz" />\r\n</u></div>\r\n<div>Our habitats contain a lot of bacteria that can causes digestive disorder in children if we do not have measures to prevent and keep him hygienic. That babies play with toys with bacteria, adopt with animals or they do not wash their hand after using toilet is the shortest way causing digestive disorders.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/digestive-disorders-children.jpg" alt="Our habitats contain a lot of bacteria that can causes digestive disorder in children" width="500" height="339" /><br />\r\n<span><em>Our habitats contain a lot of bacteria that can causes digestive disorder in children</em></span><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong><br />\r\nIII.&#160;Symptoms</strong></h3>\r\n<div>There are the most recognizable and typical signs of digestive disorder that we can list below:</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n- Bowl habits: &#160;Sudden, gradual or severe changes in bowl habits are one of the common symptoms of digestive disorders in children. The child with digestive disorders often suffer from intermittent abdominal pain, sometimes constipation, diarrhea. Constant changes in the color and the frequency of bowel movements may also indicate that the child’s digestion system has problems.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n-&#160;In addition, the child can face bloating, belching and vomiting.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/the-child-can-face-bloating.jpg" alt="The child can face bloating, belching and vomiting." width="339" height="490" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong><br />\r\nIV.&#160;Treatments</strong></h3>\r\n<div>When the child have digestive disorders, the mother should have suitable treatments for him to relive the condition of the disease. The first thing you should do is controlling your child’s diet to ensure that whether he eats something strange, unusually too sour or sweet or fatty. Parents should stop your baby’s eating that food as soon as he has abdominal pain and diarrhea.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Do hygiene for your child. Parents should teach him not to bring toy to the mouth because this activity will give bacteria the chance to attack and tell him how important to wash his hand frequently with soap.</li>\r\n    <li>Cleaning all of baby toys, the best is twice a day. With plastic items, parents should wash these toys with water and soap, and then dry them.</li>\r\n    <li>Adults who often adopt to children should keep hand clean.</li>\r\n    <li>Do not feed or force your baby as soon as realizing typical signs of digestive disorder. In reality, parents should feed the child slowly.</li>\r\n    <li>Choose fresh food, process properly to avoid food contamination. Children with digestive disorder should restrict to eat some food containing protein, fat which causes indigestion.</li>\r\n    <li>While your baby has diarrhea, parents should not avoid food such as meat, crab, shrimp, fish and still keep a normal diet because the child will be malnourished if lack of essential substance.&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>If the child have symptoms such as constant diarrhea , bleeding, fever, parents should take their children to doctor for treatment in time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>', '', 'digestive-disorders-children.jpg', '', NULL, 'digestive disorders, What is digestive disorders, Cause of digestive disorder, Symptoms of digestive disorder', 'Digestive disorder (Gastroinstestinal problems) is a term often used to refer to abnormal function of stomach. When your child encounters typical signs such as bloating, indigestion, heartburn, constipation, diarrhea or malabsorption', '2016-01-13 05:18:01', 0, 0, 2, 1),
(43, 'Childhood bedwetting', 'childhood-bedwetting', 'Ashley Rowland', '', 'Bed-wetting phenomenon occur when the bladder is full but the child unconsciously does not wake u and bed wet in his dream.', 'Bed-wetting phenomenon occur when the bladder is full but the child unconsciously does not wake u and bed wet in his dream.', '<h3><strong>I. What is bed-wetting?</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Bed-wetting (nocturnal enuresis) is the condition of involuntary urination while a child is asleep. This symptom is common in children, especially at night.&#160;</div>\r\nBed-wetting brings so many disadvantages to a child’s life and his relative, or even cause psychological problems such as shame, inferiority…If this disease lasts long, the development of a child’s psychology will be affected negatively.&#160;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>II. What causes bed-wetting?</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Bed-wetting happens when the bladder is full but the child does not wake up, as a result, he urines in his dream. Currently, the cause of bed-wetting is still not known clearly, however, this disease is often related to some causes as below:</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>The genetics: if one of parents used to suffer from bed-wetting when they were at the age of their child, the rate of bed-wetting is so high (about 40%) while both parents have history of bed-wetting, the possibility is from 70 to 75%.</li>\r\n    <li>Children with weak nerve often are unconscious and startle while sleeping. Those with these symptoms are at the higher risk of catching bed-wetting than normal ones.&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>The ability of developing bladder is not good or the bladder is too small.</li>\r\n    <li>A urinary tract infection and cystitis are the most common diseases.</li>\r\n    <li>Children with bed-wetting are premature, low birth weight, rickety, cold sweating, timid…</li>\r\n    <li>Stress: when they experience big events in life such as becoming a big brother or sister, or the first day starting school environment or sleeping away from home.</li>\r\n    <li>Parents lack motivation, or have expectations which is overwhelming to their child. This activity unintentionally put their child under pressure.</li>\r\n    <li>Parents, relatives or siblings around disparage the child, which make the condition of bed-wetting is more serious.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3><strong><br />\r\nIII.&#160;Treatments for bed-wetting in children</strong></h3>\r\n<div>When a child at the age of under 5 beds wet, parents should not be too worried. You can consult some treatments below:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Let your child eat a little soup at dinner and limit your child to drink before bed time.</li>\r\n    <li>Do not scold, berate, or tease your child. Instead, parents should help your child to understand the issue and make efforts to improve the problem. If the child does not bed wet any nights, parents should give compliment to him to make him more confident.</li>\r\n    <li>Practice: when urinating, tell your child should stop a moment and then resume.</li>\r\n    <li>The best way of dealing with bed-wetting is to consider this symptom as the slow development rather than a disease and do not drive the child to put too much attention to this problem.</li>\r\n    <li>If your child is mature and the family has adopted a variety of methods which are not effective but he still beds wet, the only thing parents have to do is not to blame, berate or scold him. If you blame the child, he will be stressed, as a result, the disease will be worsen. In this case, parents should take the child to the doctor for a urine test, ultrasound, bladder…determine the cause why this symptom happens.</li>\r\n    <li>Currently, there are some drugs that you can use for your child’s bed-wetting such as: Oxybutynin chloride; Toltero dine; Impramine; Desmopresin acetate ...However, the prescription must be follow the doctor.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\nIn addition, you can apply the following conventional remedies to treat bed-wetting in children.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\nAccording to conventional treatments of the Asian, it''s Dried longane and lichi, that play an useful roles in treating bed-wetting in children. You can find these types of dried fruits in China town.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Dried longane and lichi, the children should eat 4 to 5 fruit daily in the morning.</li>\r\n    <li>Fresh chives is fried with shrimp dishes which is served to the child.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/dried-longane.jpg" alt="Dried longane" width="250" height="168" /><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/lichi.jpg" alt="lichi" width="250" height="168" /><br />\r\n<br type="_moz" />\r\n&#160;</div>', '', 'childhood-bedwetting.jpg', '', NULL, 'How to draw a car , Draw a car, Draw a car step by step', 'Bed-wetting phenomenon occur when the bladder is full but the child unconsciously does not wake u and bed wet in his dream.', '2016-01-11 04:56:18', 0, 0, 2, 1),
(44, 'Effective treatments for coughing in children', 'effective-treatments-for-coughing-in-children', 'Ashley Rowland', '', 'Effective treatments for coughing in children', 'Cough in children is a very common disease which does not affect so much their activities in daily life but it will be difficult to cure if we can not know extract cause', '<h3><strong>I. Cough and symptoms</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Almost all most mother feel stress and worried when their child coughs, especially this condition lasts long. The wheezing and heavy breathing of their child is the obsession of each mother. However, if parents know how to supervise and listen to the baby’s cough, it is probably that they can soon understand the cause of coughing and give suitable treatments for their child in time.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>In this article, let liferespect.net show all readers some main factors that raise the risk of developing cough in children and give useful advice to treat this disease.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>A child who catches a cold usually suffer from runny nose (asphyxiation), wheezing breath, coughing, watery eyes, loss of appetite and have a fever. The level of coughing is mild, moderate or severe.</li>\r\n    <li>Allergies, asthma or external factors.</li>\r\n    <li>When inhaling dust or animal fur, some children with atopic allergy can cough constantly. With allergy, a child can have runny nose or stuffy nose.</li>\r\n    <li>A child with asthma often cough seriously at night. In addition, we can see other symptoms such as wheezing and difficulty in breath.</li>\r\n    <li>Other external factors in environment such as smoke of cigarette, air pollution. In this case, the sooner parents realize the cause of coughing in children, the more affective they can treat their child by isolating the children from these elements.</li>\r\n    <li>Pneumonia that is caused by lungs’ infection. The noticeable sign in children is coughing. If your child catch a cold, it is probably that constants coughing with difficulty in breathing and having a fever prove that you should take your baby to the hospital for a check-u immediately.</li>\r\n    <li>Sinusitis: If the coughing condition accompanied by runny nose last in two week or less, your child may suffer sinusitis. It is caused by the bacteria that invade the sinusitis, causing prolong cough. Furthermore, mucus tends to moving back the throat, causing the heavier cough.</li>\r\n    <li>Inhaled foreign body. A child experiences coughing condition for weeks without fever, runny nose or allergy, perhaps, he or she accidentally swallows or inhales toys or abnormal objects. It can cause a cough that can last for many weeks or even months until it is discovered.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<h3><strong>II. Treatments</strong></h3>\r\n<div>In the condition of capricious weather as today, children are more likely to catch respiratory disease, especially cough. That children suffering from cough without radical cure and drug- abuse will lead to counter-productiveness and side effects. Here are some natural remedies which brings nutrition not only safely but also effectively to children who suffer from cough.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<u>1.&#160;Relieve cough for children with Kumquat<br />\r\n</u><br />\r\nKumquat which contains more pectin, essential oils, sugar and vitamin can prevent inflammation, anti- virus, anti- bacteria and do expectorant. Equally important, the fruit is fresh so it trigger the digestion and cure cough.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/relieve-cough-for-children-with-kumquat.jpg" alt="Relieve cough for children with kumquat" width="500" height="329" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>How to use kumquat to cure cough.</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Clean kumquat&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Cut across the kumquat, keep the peel and seeds</li>\r\n    <li>Mix rock sugar and sugar, then put the mixes into the cooking or a steamer for 20 minutes.</li>\r\n    <li>Grind both peel and seed &#160;then let the children drink its extracts which is a little warm 3 times a day until cough is over.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<u>2.&#160;Relive cough with pear</u><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Pear has sweet, slight sour flavor, especially this fruit is used for refreshment. Most mother use pear for dessert but few know that it can cure cough in children effectively.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/how-to-use-pear-to-cure-cough.jpg" alt="How to use pear to cure cough" width="500" height="337" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>How to use pear to cure cough</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Wash pears and then cut into small pieces.</li>\r\n    <li>Cook the pear juice into concentrated ingredients, add some sugar and mix them&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Divide the ingredient after mixing into a suitable quantity in which the children can take 3-4 times a day. You should add boiling water to concentrated ingredients before the children drink.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<u>3.&#160;Relive cough with white radish</u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Cut white radish into about four to five slices, and then put them into a small pot.&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Add a bowl of water, boil the slices with small fire for 5 to 10 minutes.</li>\r\n    <li>Give your child this hot juice which can help to cure cough, dried nose, sore throat and phlegm.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/white-radish.jpg" alt="Relive cough with white radish" width="500" height="324" /><br />\r\n<div><br />\r\n<u>4.&#160;Other simple treatments to prevent cough in children</u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Wash your child’s hand frequently. It is said that about 80 percent of infectious disease including common cold are spread by hand, so it’s essential for your child to wash his hand regularly.</li>\r\n    <li>Don’t let your child to adopt to smoke.</li>\r\n    <li>Provide your child with a diversity of nutritious meal to enhance his immune systems to reduce the risk of catching some disease such as common cold, sinusitis or pneumonia.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\nNote: If your child’s coughing symptoms is so heavy, you should take them to the doctor in order to have suitable treatments and if your child has to take medicine treatments which depend on your child’s cough: mild, moderate or heavy.<br type="_moz" />\r\n<br type="_moz" />\r\n<br type="_moz" />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n</div>', '', 'relieve-cough-for-children.jpg', '', NULL, 'How to make a paper airplane', 'Cough in children is a very common disease which does not affect so much their activities in daily life but it will be difficult to cure if we can not know extract cause', '2016-01-11 03:26:22', 0, 0, 2, 1),
(45, 'Autism in children, don’t let it so late', 'autism-in-children-dont-let-it-so-late', 'Ashley Rowland', '', 'Autism is a complex disorder, affecting negatively children’s abilities such as how to use language, communicate, express emotions.', 'Autism is a complex disorder, affecting negatively children’s abilities such as how to use language, communicate, express emotions.', '<div>Any parents having a baby wish that their child can develop healthily and perfectly not only in physical but also mental aspects. However, some are not lucky enough when they realize that their child has abnormal signs in daily life. It is said that one in a hundred people in the USA have autism. Raising children with autism is a challenging but incredible journey.&#160;</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>The symptoms of this disease in children is diverse in many way whether the children are verbal or nonverbal. So what is autism and its symptoms? Whether this disease have negative effects on your children’s life? In this essay, we will explain more about the autism and help readers how to treat and prevent it effectively.&#160;</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<h3><strong>I. What is Autism.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Autism is a brain disorder (developmental disability) that affects how a person not only communicate or relate to others but also a child can make sense of the world in nature. Autism is thought to be a genetic disorder, as it often occurs in families.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>II. Cause of Autism.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Autism is commonly by the time when a child is at the age of three, however, some cases are not diagnosed until later. In general, parents are the first one to notice the signs and often ask their pediatrician for advice. It is said that the exact causes of autism is still unclearly identified but there are some environment and complex genetic factors can list below:</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>There are some main factors that trigger autism including environment factors, genetic and &#160;parental age . There are some real cases that show the genes effect how neurons in the brain link together and communicate.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Equally important, if you have already one child with the diagnosis of autism, the risk of having a second one who will be probably suffer from autism is so high. It means that another factor increasing the risk of developing autism is family history.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>In addition, researchers also give evidence that children who usually adopt technical devices so early can increase the risk of developing autism, unintentionally driving them lazy to communicate and aware of the world around.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/children-using-ipad.jpg" alt="Children using ipad" width="500" height="347" /></div>\r\n<div><span><em>Technical devices can raise the risk of devloping a child''s autism and laiziness of &#160;interaction with the world around</em></span><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Not only the activity of adopting to technical devices but also family situation is also another main risk of causing a child to suffer from autism. Fluent violence between parents in daily life results in a child’s autism spectrum disorder. When a child experience the situation of his or her parents or relatives regularly having arguments with each other, the child will feel disappointed and unconfident to have connection with society. They will no longer be happy and comfortable to take part in community activities.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/domestic-violence-with-children.jpg" alt="Domestic violence with children" width="500" height="282" /></div>\r\n<div><span><em>Domestic violence with children</em></span></div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Environmental factors have been even more difficult to identify whether they cause autism or not. So far there is little evidence that would suggest that any environmental factor significantly results in this disease in children. In addition, parents with high age not only does seem to increase risk for developing autism but also other negative conditions.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<h3><strong>IV. Symptoms of autism</strong></h3>\r\n<div>The main symptoms of autism spectrum disorder is the problems with communication and social interaction.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>a. <u>Spoken language</u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Delay in speech development. In detail, a normal child will speak at least 10 different words at the age of two</span>&#160;<span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">while the child with autism disorder cannot say a full sentence.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Constant repetition of phrases and set words.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Flat or monotonous or flat speed.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Preferring to communicate with single words, although they can speak in sentences.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<div><u>b.&#160;<span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Respond to others</span></u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Not interact with the people call their name despite of not facing any hearing problems.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Negatively unusual react to someone’s asking them to do something</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Reject their parents’ affection or cuddles.<br />\r\n    </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><span class="Apple-tab-span" span=""> </span><br />\r\n<div><u>c.&#160;<span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Interaction with others</span></u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Not aware of others’ individual space or being unusually intolerant and irritated when other enter their own world.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Avoid eye contact</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Avoid crowding and noisy environment or situation that other normal child prefer such as birthday party.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Prefer playing alone instead of asking others to play with them</span></li>\r\n    <li>Rarely use body language- facial expression or gestures when communicate.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div><u>d.&#160;<span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Behaviour</span></u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Repeat their constant movements such as flicking their fingers, flapping their hands or rocking back and ford.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Play with toy in a repeated and uncreative way such as line the block up in the order of color or size rather than use them to build a house or set a car.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Not prefer something new, any changes such as they can eat a repeated menu without any recommend of different receipt to trigger their appetite.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Prefer to have the same routine and get angry if there are any changes.<br />\r\n    </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><span class="Apple-tab-span" span=""> <br />\r\n<h3><strong>IV. Treatments&#160;</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Any child with autism will have different manifestation, therefore there is no special treatment for all cases. Parents should choose the following treatment to apply appropriately to your child.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Restrict children to adopt to technical devices such as smartphone, ipad...instead, parents should have a chat with their child daily</li>\r\n    <li>Try to avoid violence in your family because the future of you children deepend on the family''s happiness</li>\r\n    <li>Medication: medicine plays an effective role in control disease. Providing a full range of essential vitamins and balanced diets will help children reduce the vibrations in the nervous system. Besides, antidepressants and nerve tonic also help them to be more stable.</li>\r\n    <li>Communication remedy: communication therapy will make the children have creation in using language, limit other forms of non-verbal communication. For example, parents should say to their child with simple words or sentences but with clear and slow pause between words to motivate the children to mimic and have time to process information. Equally important, encouragement and motivation of communication will provoke them to overcome emotional and psychology barriers, increasing their social interaction. Their sense, feeling and opinion will be developed fully by social stories in which everything happens in nature. It is normally indicated that &#160;parents should spend more time and patience to talk to their child with autism disorder. When parents are close and usually have a talk with their children, they will forget and lose shy, scare in communication.</li>\r\n    <li>Behaviour therapy: with this treatment, the level of a child’s mimic actions, inappropriate behavior and aggression will be reduced. This therapy is applied based on the belief that it will break some unchanged habits by building some new ones. Parents can guide children to handle some certain and typical behavior, often encouraging &#160;and rewarding each time they have been performing the best. &#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Parents support programs: The parents can try The EarlyBird- offered by The National Autistic Society- the program is for the pre-school child. When entering this campaign, parents are supported an useful advice on how to take care their child with autism and help them to improve their skills.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n</span>Treatment in children diagnosed with autism diagnosis is a difficult and challenging &#160;period, it brings insecurity, anxiety in both parent and children. Despite being incurable, early diagnosis and intervention can be useful to help autistic children to have &#160;better develop and improve our lives.<span class="Apple-tab-span" span=""><br type="_moz" />\r\n<br type="_moz" />\r\n<div><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', 'autism-in-children.jpg', '', NULL, 'Autism in children, What is autism?', 'Autism is a complex disorder, affecting negatively children’s abilities such as how to use language, communicate, express emotions.', '2016-01-07 05:16:27', 0, 0, 2, 1),
(46, 'Asthma in children and infants', 'asthma-in-children-and-infants', 'Ashley Rowland', '', 'Asthma in Children and Infants', 'Asthma is a long-term condition that has negative impacts on your airways that make individuals have difficulty in breathing.&#160;', '<div>I. What is Asthma?</div>\r\n<div>Asthma is a chronic condition that involves in the constriction of the airway of the respiratory system, resulting in coughing, wheezing, breathlessness and chest tightness.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>It is caused by the inflammation of the description of mucus in the inner linings of the air vessels. Perfume, allergens, tobacco smoke, emotional stress or exercises are the most noticeable factors that trigger asthma attack. For some people, asthma is only a minor nuisance while others consider that this disease limits their daily activities. Asthma cannot be curable but it can be controlled if you are patient enough to be under the doctor’s instruction of treatment.</div>\r\n&#160;', '', 'children-asthma.jpg', '', NULL, 'How to make a paper boat, Paper boat', 'Asthma is a long-term condition that has negative impacts on your airways that make individuals have difficulty in breathing.', '2016-01-13 04:19:50', 0, 36, 3, 1),
(62, 'Signs of prematurity that pregnant women need to know', 'signs-of-prematurity-that-pregnant-women-need-to-know', 'Don Miller', '', 'Signs of prematurity that pregnant women need to know', 'The period of pregnancy is the time that mom and her baby is the weakest, there are so many internal and external impacts that can results in prematurity, especially from 27th to 37th weeks of pregnancy', 'Meanwhile, there are about 40% cases of prematurity that even experts cannot determine the cause. Therefore, if you are pregnant, you need to recognize the symptoms of prematurity to have appropriate and immediate treatment to minimize the risk of prematurity.&#160;\r\n<div><br />\r\n<h3><strong>1. Increase vaginal discharge</strong></h3>\r\n<div>If you suddenly realize that the vagina is always moist, mucus or bleeding (perhaps, bloods are scattered) and sucks your paints. Therefore, you need to see the obstetrician to have a check because this symptoms can be considered as the risk of prematurity.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>2. The appearance of contractions</strong></h3>\r\n<div>If pregnant women see the contractions in their lower abdomen in connection with muscle contractions accompanied by cramps or bleeding in the vagina in that is not due to diarrhea, certainly, they face the problems of having a prematurity birth.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/signs-of-prematurity.jpg" alt="The appearance of contractions" width="500" height="334" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>3. Emerge of lower-back pain</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Pregnant women have to encounter lower back pain more intensively while previously they cannot see this symptom. It means that your pregnancy face problems and you need to call obstetrician for particular heath check. This is one of the symptom for prematurity.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/emerge-of-lower-back-pain.jpg" alt="Emerge of lower-back pain" width="500" height="372" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>4. Increasing pressure on the area of innominate-bone</strong></h3>\r\n<div>This phenomenon which is similar to the incidence of giving birth is due to the fetus deeply slipping, weighing on the area of innominate-bone leading the pregnant women’s sensation of heaviness.&#160;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/pregnant-woman.jpg" alt="Pregnant woman" width="500" height="332" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>5. The sensation of nausea</strong></h3>\r\n<div>If women are pregnant from 20th to 37th weeks, they feel giddy, sicken and face the phenomenon of diarrhea. As a result, this is a worse symptom for the fetus, which can result in prematurity.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/the-sensation-of-nausea.jpg" alt="The sensation of nausea" width="500" height="476" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>6. The activity of fetus reduces.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Pregnant women test themselves by lying down and tracking their baby’s activities. If your baby has not 10 movements within 2 hours, you should make an appointment with the obstetrician to find out the reason.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/the-activity-of-fetus-reduces.jpg" alt="The activity of fetus reduces" width="500" height="383" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>7. The rupture of amniotic fluid</strong></h3>\r\n<div>This phenomenon depends on each individuals. While someone account for dipping in the rupture of amniotic fluid, a few flow freely. You should pay special attention to this case that when facing this serious symptom, &#160;you need to come to the nearest hospital for diagnosis and treatments otherwise this will have negative effect on your live.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/the-rupture-of-amniotic-fluid.jpg" alt="The rupture of amniotic fluid" width="500" height="341" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>8. Some measures to prevent prematurity.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Although there are many drugs to prevent prematurity, the results are not always successful, so prevention is better than treatment.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<ol>\r\n    <li>Pregnant women should eradicate some risk factors such as give up smoking, treatments of infections such as urinary tract infections, vaginitis ...</li>\r\n    <li>Take care of antenatal, ensure balance and adequate. Lack of nutrition is the cause of beginning labor and prematurity.&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Practice some gentle exercises, however, avoid exercise with high intensity during pregnant period.</li>\r\n    <li>Smoke and wine are the cause of prematurity and preventing the development of the fetus, therefore, pregnant women need to quit this habit.</li>\r\n    <li>Semen contains prostaglandins and its presence in the vagina can cause uterine contractions. The contraction usually occurs after uterine orgasms. Therefore, you have no need to abstain from sexual intercourse during normal pregnancy but should avoid intercourse during pregnancy when you are at risk of prematurity.</li>\r\n    <li>Pregnant women should do to hospital for a check when you begin to labor and have some symptoms such as: back pain, abnormal vaginal drainage or diarrhea. Early diagnosis is the best opportunity for successful treatment.</li>\r\n    <li>Vaginitis and cervical can cause prematurity and the rupture of amniotic fluid, therefore, pregnant women should have periodic examination to have appropriate treatments if suffering these diseases. Urinary tract infections such as pyelonephritis is frequently associated with high risk of prematurity.</li>\r\n    <li>The internal medicine complications like high blood pressure disease, diabetes if being monitored and responded appropriately will avoid many cases to specify early termination of pregnancy.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>', '', 'pregnant-women-9-month.jpg', '', NULL, 'Signs of prematurity, Pregnant women', 'The period of pregnancy is the time that mom and her baby is the weakest, there are so many internal and external impacts that can results in prematurity, especially from 27th to 37th weeks of pregnancy', '2016-01-29 09:53:17', 0, 78, 3, 1),
(63, 'Beneficial foods and drink beneficial during pregnancy', 'beneficial-foods-and-drink-beneficial-during-pregnancy', 'Don Miller', '', 'Beneficial foods and drink beneficial during pregnancy', 'There are some fast foods which do good for pregnant women’s health. You can consider them a snack to provide extra nutrition and energy for health. Here are eight tasty kind of foods that you should intake during pregnant period.&#160;', '<h3><strong>1. Fruits</strong></h3>\r\n<div>In general, fruits are really good for human, especially pregnant women’s health in particular. fruits are like fresh vegetables, which is considered as an indispensable source of food for pregnant women.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>The ingredients in fruits help the mother and her baby healthy and reduce the risk of anemia during pregnancy.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>They can intake some fruits such as apple, pears, oranges, bananas, custard-apple…drink these smoothies or juices is highly recommended because they are full of nutrition, which help you healthier and energize you during pregnancy. additionally, these type of fruits are digestible, good for pregnant women and their baby.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>You can choose the kind of fruits that you really love, and each brings different benefits such as orange, lemon, grapefruit ... are rich in vitamin c, which act as healthy gums, increase immunity for the body.</div>', '', 'beneficial-foods-during-pregnancy.jpg', '', NULL, 'Beneficial foods and drink beneficial during pregnancy', 'There are some fast foods which do good for pregnant women’s health. You can consider them a snack to provide extra nutrition and energy for health. Here are eight tasty kind of foods that you should intake during pregnant period.', '2016-01-29 10:00:54', 0, 78, 3, 1),
(56, 'Eardrum rupture', 'eardrum-rupture', 'Don Miller', '', 'Ruptured eardrum is a result of ear infections which is not treated and lasts for a long time.', 'Ruptured eardrum is a result of ear infections which is not treated and lasts for a long time. In particular, one of the most common cause is middle-ear infection.', '<h3><strong>I. What is eardrum rupture?</strong></h3>\r\n<div>A ruptured eardrum (perforated tympanic membrane) is a tear or hole in the eardrum. The eardrum separating the outer and middle ear canal is a thin piece off tissue.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Eardrum rupture can not only cause hearing loss and but also make the middle ear vulnerable to infection or other injury.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Ruptured eardrum often heals within a few weeks without treatment. Sometimes, you may need a procedure to promote healing of tympanic membrane rupture, or need surgery to repair the eardrum burst.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<h3><strong>II.&#160;Symptoms of eardrum rupture.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>There are many typical signs and symptoms of ruptured eardrum including:<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li>Earache emerge suddenly and usually disappear quickly</li>\r\n    <li>Bloody drainage &#160;from ear</li>\r\n    <li>Hearing loss</li>\r\n    <li>Tinnitus&#160;</li>\r\n    <li>Spinning sensation</li>\r\n    <li>Nausea or vomiting, which may result from spinning sensation.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\nYou should call the doctor if you see any abnormal signs and symptoms of ruptured eardrum or any pain in your ears.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3><strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIII.Causes of ruptured eardrum</strong></h3>\r\n<div><u><em><strong>The eardrum has two main functions:<br />\r\n<br type="_moz" />\r\n</strong></em></u></div>\r\n<div>-<span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Role of hearing: when the sound wave attacks, the eardrum vibrates - the first step in the structure of the middle and the inner ear translate sound waves into nerve impulses.<br />\r\n&#160;</span></div>\r\n<div>-<span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Role of protecting: The eardrum also acts as a protective barrier between the ears from water, bacteria and other foreign substances.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div><u><em><strong>The cause of the rupture the eardrum, also known as tympanic, may include:<br />\r\n<br type="_moz" />\r\n</strong></em></u></div>\r\n<div>-&#160;<em>Mid-ear infection</em>: Middle ear infection often leads to an accumulation of fluid in the middle ear. The pressure from the fluid can cause the eardrum.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>-&#160;<em>Barotrauma</em>. Barotrauma is the stress which is exerted on the eardrum when the air pressure in the middle ear and the environment is out of balance. If the pressure is so severe, the eardrum can perforate. Barotrauma is usually caused by changes in air pressure associated with air travel. Besides, there are some events that cause the changes in pressure, as result, leading to eardrum rupture such as scuba diving, direct blow to the ear..<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>-&#160;<em>Loud noise or explosion (sound trauma)</em>.A loud noise or explosion such as an explosion or gunshot - essentially a sound wave is so severe that it can cause eardrum broken.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>-&#160;<em>Small objects</em>: bobby pin or swab can puncture or tear the eardrum.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>-&#160;<em>Serious head injury</em>. Serious injuries, such as skull fractures, can cause instability or damage to inner ear structures, including the eardrum.</div>\r\n</span></div>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>IV.Complications</strong></h3>\r\n<div>- &#160;<em>Hearing loss</em>: In general, patients with rupture eardrum can suffer from hearing loss for a long time The size and location of the tear can affect the degree of hearing loss.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>- &#160;<em>Middle ear infections</em>: Rupture eardrum enables bacteria enter the ear. If the eardrum does not heal, this can constantly vulnerable (chronic) infection that can cause permanent hearing loss.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>- &#160;<em>Cholesteatoma</em>. Cholesteatoma is a cyst in the middle ear consisting of other debris and the skin cells. Ear canal debris normally travels to your outer ear with the aid of ear-protecting earwax. If your eardrum is ruptured, the skin debris can pass into your middle ear and form a cyst. Cholesteatoma provide a friendly environment for bacteria and contain the protein which can damage the bones of the middle ear.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>V.&#160;Treatments</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Most rupture eardrum can heal itself without treatment within a few weeks. If the laceration or puncture of the eardrum cannot heal, here are some recommendations including below:</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Eardrum patch. If the eardrum tear or cannot self-close, an ENT specialist can seal it with a paper patch. A chemical will be applied to stimulate the development of the edges of the cuts and then apply a patch over the hole. The procedure may need to be repeated three or four times before the hole closes.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Surgery: If ruptured eardrum is not treated effectively by a patch, the patients will be recommended the treatment of surgery. One of the most common surgical procedure is called tympanoplasty Surgeons transplant a small patch of skin through the eardrum. This procedure is performed on an outpatient basis, which means that you can go home at the same day.<br />\r\n    </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div><span class="Apple-tab-span" span=""> &#160;</span></div>\r\n<div><u>Lifestyle and home remedies.<br type="_moz" />\r\n</u></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Keep your ear dry while ruptured eardrum is cured. Put a cotton ball with lubricating oil into the ear while have a bath.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Do not clean the ear. Let your eardrum heal by time passing</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Avoid blowing your nose. The pressure generated when blowing your nose can damage eardrums heal.</span></li>\r\n    <li><span class="Apple-tab-span" span="">Protect your ear against excessive noise by wearing protective earplugs earmuffs in your workplace.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', '', '', NULL, 'Eardrum rupture', 'Ruptured eardrum is a result of ear infections which is not treated and lasts for a long time. In particular, one of the most common cause is middle-ear infection.', '2016-01-29 06:31:30', 0, 84, 6, 1);
INSERT INTO `tbl_posts` (`post_id`, `post_title`, `post_title_rewrite`, `post_author`, `post_source`, `post_shotinfo`, `post_info`, `post_value`, `post_tags`, `post_image`, `post_picture`, `post_status`, `post_keys`, `post_des`, `post_date`, `type_id`, `cago_id`, `cate_id`, `user_id`) VALUES
(57, 'Healthy diets for healthy life', 'healthy-diets-for-healthy-life', 'Don Miller', '', 'Healthy diets for healthy life', 'A healthy body which is immune to illness is commonly human’s desire. Some “pocket” secret below will help you achieve healthy weight for healthy life without affecting your pockets at all.', '<h3><strong>1. Maintain an appropriate diets.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Eating is an indispensible need for people in daily life. Moreover, eating habits have direct affect and is a crucial elements for your health.&#160;</div>\r\n<div>We cannot gave a specific quantity for your diets and daily amount of water for anyone because everyone has his own need. Depending on the state of health, the degree of physical activities and the aspects of work that individuals have appropriate diets.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>However, there are general principles for people having eating habits which is significantly beneficial for health. You should eat more fruits and vegetables for a better health and limiting the risk of chronic diseases or cancer. The habits of consuming too much delicious and nutritious food from animal meat for a long time will cause dangerous diseases such as hyperlipidemia in which the fat levels in blood is high, diabetes, hypertension, or cancer..</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>2. Maintain a healthy weight</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Obesity is noticeably concerned issue in our society. People who are overweight and obese are at high risk of dangerous diseases such as diabetes, hypertension, cardiovascular and stroke. Therefore, the activity of maintain weight for appropriate height and physique is also an essential requirement to achieve stable health.&#160;</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Suitable diet in combination with regular exercise and sports are effective measures to control weight. If you realize any abnormalities in your weight (even if adopting diets and exercise), you need to see a doctor to get a proper advice.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/maintain-a-healthy-weight-for-life.png" alt="maintain a healthy weight for life" width="500" height="381" /><br />\r\nMaintain a healthy weight for life<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>3. Regular exercises</strong></h3>\r\n<div>The common trend in many countries nowadays is the laziness of doing exercise. In the USA, it is statistically about 50% of men and women below the level of physical activity required. Regular exercises will help you feel relaxed and refresh yourself.&#160;</div>\r\n<div>In adulthood, you should do exercise at least 30 minutes everyday. You can practice a certain exercise which is repeated daily, or you can change the form of exercise as long as you feel fascinated with.&#160;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/regular-exercises-for-health.png" alt="Regular exercises for health" width="500" height="270" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>4. Periodic health check.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Whether you comply well to diets, exercises &#160;and daily activities are beneficial to your body weight at your age, but, you should not be so subjective, because may be there are some dangerous elements that put your health in danger.</div>\r\n<div>Period health check will help you to detect diseases early (if any) and this habit will be essential requirement so you can always be the active individual of supervising your health.&#160;</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Equally important, do not forget to inject vaccine for yourself and your family to fight the risk of catching any diseases.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/periodic-health-check.jpg" alt="Periodic health check" width="500" height="334" /></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>5. Actively reduce stress</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Stress at work and in family is absolutely a large issue that affect individuals’ health and standard of livings.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>The only thing you should do to relieve stress is doing exercise, entertaining yourself by going to the theater, chatting with family and friends to solve the problems or commonly simplify all the problems in life to create spiritual medicine in controlling the press at work that you have to face everyday.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/actively-reduce-stress.jpg" alt="Actively reduce stress" width="500" height="332" /></div>\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', 'healthy-diets-for-healthy-life.png', '', NULL, 'Living healthy, Fitness & exercise, Food & Recipes, Healthy diets for healthy life', 'A healthy body which is immune to illness is commonly human’s desire. Some pocket secret below will help you achieve healthy weight for healthy life without affecting your pockets at all.', '2016-01-26 07:31:01', 0, 75, 4, 1),
(58, '12 exercises - for 12 different mood', '12-exercises-for-12-different-mood', 'Don Miller', '', '12 exercises - for 12 different mood', 'All exercises are intended to help you stay healthy. But each exercise will work specifically for each mental state.&#160;', '<h3><strong>1. If you are in anger, do some kickboxing</strong></h3>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/girl-boxing.jpg" alt="Girl kixboxing" width="500" height="326" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nWhen you are angry, your face turns red, calories want to be liberated. Jennipher Walters, coach of FitBottomedGirls.com gives advice that when you are angry or upset, a great way to escape this mood is kickboxing. Bring your anger to hit straight and direct to punching bags will help you feel more comfortable.</div>\r\n<div>\r\n<h3><strong><br />\r\n<br />\r\n2.&#160;Do a walk to reduce anxiety.</strong></h3>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/do-a-walk-to-reduce-anxiety.jpg" alt="Do a walk to reduce anxiety" width="500" height="253" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nHave a walk is one of the most effective way to release your anxiety. Walking for just a few minutes could soothe your nerves and boost your mood in a positive direction, especially if you walk outdoors.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>3.&#160;Being exhausted, please try Tai Chi</strong></h3>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/tai-chi.jpg" alt="Being exhausted, please try Tai Chi" width="500" height="323" /></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\nWhen you are lack of energy, you should avoid physical exercise. Instead, try to shifting your focus and energize the body with Tai Chi. Tai Chi plays an important role in giving supplement to your body, improve the quality of sleeping, reduce stress and enhance your sensation of happiness. These factors can prevent your feeling of being exhausted.&#160;<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>4.&#160;If alone, try a Barre class.</strong></h3>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/barre-classes-for-you.jpg" alt="If alone, try a Barre class" width="500" height="218" /></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\nThis type of exercise is related to ballet and aesthetics. The classes are often organized in groups, therefore, when you feel lonely, joining the barre class is definitely an ideal solution. Entering this class, you will have chance to make an acquaintance with others in a friendly and funny environment.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>5. Ride bicycle can relieve stress.</strong></h3>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/ride-bicycle-can-relieve-stress.jpg" alt="Ride bicycle can relieve stress" width="500" height="298" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nCycling in the yard or in the street play an essential part in reducing stress by increasing endorphin hormone - the hormone of happiness. In addition, this activity can obviously shorten or drive you to reduce thinking, so, your stress condition will be handled in a better way. Tackling these challenges on a cycling route &#160;( uphill, downhill..) appears to make you feel more confident and capable of handling the pressure better.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>6. If you are stuff, try to have a jog.</strong></h3>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/try-to-go-jogging.jpg" alt="Try to go jogging" width="500" height="317" /><br />\r\nYou can refresh yourself by jogging<br />\r\n<br />\r\nYou try to solve a problem in vain or give an idea but not satisfactory? Stop what you are doing, instead, go out and have a jog. The repetition of each running step allows the brain to relax because at this time, your brain can not process any complex information. The activity of jogging can improve your mentality by increasing the amount of endorphins.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>7.&#160;If you are in the mood of anxiety, enter yoga class.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>You feel scared and worried? yoga will be the most ideal exercise help you forget the confusion.</div>\r\n<div>With yoga, you can feel peaceful in your mind and reduce your stress as well as anxiety. Through breathing and inhaling steadily, your body will focus on regular rhythm. Then &#160;Hence the idea of chance, worries will melt away.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/yoga-class.jpg" alt="Yoga class for woman" width="500" height="250" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>8. Try high-intensive &#160;physical exercises when you feeling rushed.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Chris Freytag - Fitness Specialist certified by the Board American fitness gives advice that “ If you are under pressure of time, try HIIT (high-intensity exercise) such as running, cycling, jogging..You perform the exercise for a short time, and then have a rest, which will help you to relieve the sensation of hurry.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/high-intensive-physical.jpg" alt="Try high-intensive  physical exercises when you feeling rushed." width="500" height="406" /><br />\r\nTry high-intensive &#160;physical exercises when you feeling rushed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>9.&#160;Practice some physical strength with high intensive.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>We have a difficult decision that weighs on your mind? A study published in the Archives of Internal Medicine in USA showed that regular strength training can help women improve mental focus and attention. At this time, your brain focus on the workouts so your feelings will also benefit from a more capable orientation. Physical exercise are lifting weights with high intensity.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/practice-some-physical-strength.jpg" alt="Practice some physical strength with high intensive" width="500" height="327" /></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>10.&#160;If you are interested, please try to climb the stairs</strong></h3>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/climb-the-stairs.jpg" alt="If you are interested, please try to climb the stairs" width="500" height="330" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nClimbing stairs which drives you sweated should give you more inspiration. This activity not only consumed many calories but also practice you the ability of enduring challenge.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>11. Dance if you are sad.&#160;</strong><span class="Apple-tab-span" span=""><br />\r\n</span></h3>\r\n<div><span class="Apple-tab-span" span=""> <br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/girl-dancing.jpg" alt="Dance if you are sad." width="500" height="327" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nMusic and exercise should help you increase endorphins which is resistant to depression and sadness. You do not have to enter a dancing class, you can dance alone at your beloved house. Certainly, you can reduce a significant amount of stress. You just relax yourself and let the body move in music.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<h3><strong>12.&#160;If you are full of energy, try zumba</strong></h3>\r\n<div><span class="Apple-tab-span" span=""> <br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/zumba-exercises.jpg" alt="If you are full of energy, try zumba" width="500" height="331" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nIf you are full of energy today, do some zumba exercises, it will help you to make the best use of your energy to start a new day more effectively. The cheerful rhythm of zumba inspire you &#160;immediately and follow you all day.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', 'yoga-class-for-health.jpg', '', NULL, '12 exercises, for 12 different mood', 'All exercises are intended to help you stay healthy. But each exercise will work specifically for each mental state.', '2016-01-27 04:04:02', 0, 74, 4, 1),
(59, 'Recommedation of the anti cancer foods', 'recommedation-of-the-anti-cancer-foods', 'Don Miller', '', 'Recommedation of the anti cancer foods', 'One of the factors that cause cancer is the diet. According to the World Health Organization, 30 percent of people with cancer is related to unhealthy diets. The American Cancer Society recommends that you should eat the right amount of food to keep fit and eat at least five servings of fruits and vegetables a day to increase your immune system.', 'More evidence has shown that the regular absorption of foods which contain fat, butter milk, bacon can result in cancer, especially colorectal cancer. However, green vegetables, nuts and fresh fruit contain a lot of antioxidant, vitamin, fibers which contribute to reduce the incidence of disease. Certain foods may be beneficial in protecting you from cancer. Your diet should be included the following foods and drinks to fight cancer.\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>1.&#160;Tomatoes.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Some studies has indicated that tomatoes contain a type of carotenoid and red pigment called Lycopene and Beta carotene (natural vitamin A), which contributes to combat oxidative. Therefore, tomatoes play an essential role in preventing cancer.&#160;</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/tomato-anti-cancer-foods.jpg" alt="Tomato anti cancer foods" width="500" height="332" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe researchers found that tomatoes are beneficial in preventing some cancer such as breast cancer, gastritis cancer and gastrointestinal cancer. According to John Erdman of the University of Illinois (USA)- the professor emeritus of the department of food science&#160;and human nutrition, to prevent cancers, especially &#160;prostate cancer, people should eat raw tomatoes.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/tomato-juice.jpg" alt="Tomato juice reduces body fat" width="500" height="394" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>2.&#160;Kiwi</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Kiwi is rich of vitamin, especially vitamin C with the content &#160;four t twelve, thirty and sixty times higher than citrus, apple and grape, respectively.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/kiwi-for-health.jpg" alt="Kiwi is rich of vitamin, especially vitamin C" width="500" height="329" /><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Through recent research, kiwis contain a type of active substances which prevent the formation of carcinogenic substances in the body. In general, this kind of fruit is a beneficial treatments for cancer.&#160;</div>\r\n<br />\r\nMoreover, kiwi also &#160;contains flavonoids and carotenoids (antioxidants compounds). These compounds play an important role in protecting the DNA from being damaged by oxidation, therefore, the development of cancer would be prevented and curbed.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>3. Cruciferous vegetables</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Cruciferous Vegetables in which the group contains cabbage. Broccoli and cauliflower may be remarkably helpful in preventing you from cancer, especially, broccoli contains a significant amount of sulforaphane , motivates &#160;the growth of the enzyme to protect the body and excretes carcinogenic chemicals. Meanwhile, compounds-indole-3-carbinol in cabbage prevents the development of breast cancer.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/cruciferous-vegetables.jpg" alt="Cruciferous Vegetables" width="500" height="299" /><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Broccoli helps fight breast, prostate, liver, &#160;skin, bladder, lung, &#160;stomach cancer. You should add broccoli regularly in the daily menu.</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>4. Green tea</strong></h3>\r\nDrink a cup of green tea or more a day can help to fight cancer, especially lung cancer which is caused by smoking. Green tea leaves have an abundant source of antioxidant called catechin that protects body cells. Both black and green &#160;teas contain catechins but green tea is a better choice to prevent cancer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/green-tea.jpg" alt="Green tea health benefits" width="500" height="333" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>5.&#160;Garlic.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Garlic is considered the healthiest herb in the world and an useful treatments for cancer, &#160;including breast cancer.&#160;<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Garlic is rich of sulfur, arginine, oligosaccharides, flavonoids and selenium. Health experts in the USA have recommended that women should use garlic to prevent and control breast cancer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/garlic-cloves.jpg" alt="Garlic cloves" width="500" height="333" /></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<div>Garlic and allyl sulfur components of its organic proven effective inhibiting the progression of cancer cells. The most interesting &#160;effect of garlic is &#160;that a specific tissue or a specific carcinogen is not limited. Reduced activation of carcinogens is the primary attribution.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>The appropriate mechanism of AND replication is crucial in the prevention and control of cancer, including breast cancer. Extract of garlic is proven to be effective in promoting positive action of DNA replication mechanisms.</div>\r\n<h3><strong><br />\r\n6. Turmeric</strong></h3>\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/turmeric.jpg" alt="Turmeric" width="500" height="373" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nRecently, Studies have been proved that turmeric contains main substance called curcumin which effectively destructs cancer cell steadily and inhibits the activation of NF-Kappa B signal. Clinical trial result has shown that turmeric is remarkably useful in preventing a wide range of cancers such as: skin, mouth, esophagus, stomach and colon cancer.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>7. Aubergine</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Modern science has explored that the component of solanine in aubergine can prevent the development of tumors in the digestive system. Moreover, aubergine contains a substance &#160;called nightshade soda- one component also can protect humans from cancer.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/aubergine.jpg" alt="Aubergine" width="500" height="366" /><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>According to America experts, aubergine juice has many active ingredients which is capable of preventing stomach cancer. In addition, this type of food &#160;contains a large amount of fiber which &#160;particularly useful in the treatment of colon cancer. Therefore, experts recommend that you should make a room for aubergine in your daily diet.</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>8. Grape</strong></h3>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/grape.jpg" alt="Grape" width="500" height="312" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nGrape is a kind of fruit which is absolutely effective in inhabiting cancer. Grapes contain high amount of caffeic acid, an anti-cancer effect. In addition, grape also contains bioflavonoids that help healthy cells able to fight and kill cancer cells. Nutrient resveratrol in grapes also play an important role in protecting &#160;the body from a wide range of cancer, especially liver, lung, breast and prostate cancer.<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>9. Beans</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Beans are good for our health, therefore, it is the fact that bean can protect our body from cancer. Beans contain powerful phytochemicals which can protect the body''s cells against damage that can lead to cancer. In the laboratory, these compounds slow down the tumor growth and prevent tumors from causing physical damage to neighboring cells.<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/kidney-beans.jpg" alt="Kidney beans" width="500" height="296" /><br />\r\n<h3><strong>10. Asparagus</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Asparagus is defined as containing different active glutathione (GSH), an antioxidant with anti-cancer properties which should be able to prevent and cure cancer. The component of asparagine in this type of vegetable essential for the construction of cell division and enhances the effectiveness of cancer treatment.&#160;</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/asparagus.jpg" alt="Asparagus" width="500" height="333" /><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Research shows that glutathione enhances your T cells, regulates the immune system and improves against the attack of the disease, while protecting your tissues and controlling autoimmune reactions .</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<div>Asparagus &#160;that prevent against toxins of glutathione cell helps eliminate carcinogens. It continuously control your cells and seeks to prevent diseases, toxins, viruses, pollutants, radiation, drugs and oxidative stress.</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n</div>', '', 'cruciferous-vegetables.jpg', '', NULL, 'The anti cancer foods, Recommedation foods', 'Recommedation of the anti cancer foods. Some kind of foods are highly recommeded in your daily meal', '2016-01-27 05:22:52', 0, 75, 4, 1),
(60, 'Eating habits to prevent disease', 'eating-habits-to-prevent-disease', 'Don Miller', '', 'Eating habits to prevent disease', 'It is vital for you to have appropriate diets which play an important role in not only balancing the nutrition in your body but also supply full energy for physical activities.', 'Here are some tips for your daily diet to change your eating habits. If your eating habits are maintained regularly and daily as below, &#160;it will have positive impact on your health.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<h3><strong>1. Drink two glass of water daily before each meal</strong></h3>\r\n<div>This beneficial habit not only ensure that your body is in the condition of being supplied enough water but also help to control the amount of food you digest. An America study has shown that drinking two cups of water before each meal can reduce hunger and food intake, which can keep you slim.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/drink-much-water-in-the-midday.jpg" alt="Drink much water in the midday" width="500" height="263" /><br />\r\n<em>Drink much water in the midday</em><br />\r\n&#160;<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>2. Add coffee to milk</strong></h3>\r\n<div>It is not the same as adding milk to coffee. &#160;The first thing when you wake up is pouring a glass of skim milk. Then drink 1/5 cup, after that you should add the coffee to the rest glass that you drink. By following this tip, you can recharge 25% of vitamin D and 30% calcium necessary for the body each day.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/add-coffee-to-milk.jpg" alt="Add coffee to milk" width="500" height="330" /></div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>3. Drink a glass of water after a meal full of fast foods</strong></h3>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/drink-a-glass-of-ater.jpg" alt="Drink a glass of water after a meal full of fast foods" width="500" height="331" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe amount of calorines and salt in fast foods often exceed the permissible standards. Although after intaking fast food, our body are loaded into so much belly fat, but a glass of water can help you liberate the concentration of sodium in the body, help you avoid high blood pressure.</div>\r\n<div><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>4. Try to eat onion each day</strong></h3>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/onion.jpg" alt="Try to eat onion each day" width="500" height="301" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nMany people are afraid to eat vegetables such as chives or buld, especially onion anh this is not a good eating habit because onions contain a large amount of flavonoids help protect the heart. Therefore, nutritionists in the USA recommend that individuals should eat onions daily as a habit. Especially, when you eat dishes such as steak, this kind of food is considered as “breeches-buoy “ to reduce toxins entering your body from barbecue.<br />\r\n</div>\r\n<h3><strong>5. Drink iced tea.</strong></h3>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/drink-iced-tea.jpg" alt="Drink iced tea every day" width="500" height="333" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nA recent study of US agriculture department discovered that in addition to green vegetables and carrots, red tea contains many antioxidants which may help you resist the intrusion of wrinkles and cancer effectively. Cold water can make the material useful in this tea undestroyed, but slowly melting, the only thing you should do is just wait a bit for the cold tea.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>6. Have a snack at 3 pm</strong></h3>\r\n<div><img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/have-a-snack-at-3-pm.jpg" alt="Have a snack at 3 pm" width="500" height="321" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nThe reason for you to cutting the breakfast is that may be you oversleep, however, it is beneficial if you have a snack at 3 pm every day. Nutritional supplement in the period between lunch and dinner, can help you to overcome fatigue during &#160;the time of ending day. Yogurt, fruit, biscuits are great choices.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>7. Eating oranges even white part of dried orange peel.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Many people often eating oranges throwing the dried orange peel without knowing that fact white part of orange is rich in flavonoids - an antioxidant that is beneficial for the body. So let''s change the eating habits of oranges from today.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/dried-orange-peel.jpg" alt="Eating oranges even white part of dried orange peel" width="500" height="314" /></div>\r\n<div><em>Eating oranges even white part of dried orange peel.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<br />\r\n</em>\r\n<h3><strong>8. Schedule to drink water each day</strong></h3>\r\n<div>Busy work can make you thirsty, which can drive your body in the condition of lacking water to supply. As a result, you face some health problems such as dry skin, dizziness, fatigue.. &#160;Therefore, you should preset a water bottle around 1.5l, and remember drink it regularly.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>9.&#160;Buying fruits with umber color.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>There are a wide rage of fruits, however, fruits with umber is the most beneficial for your health, including grapes, plums…because these types of fruits contain a lot of antioxidants.&#160;</div>\r\n<div>&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>10.&#160;Avoid fats in dinner</strong></h3>\r\n<div><br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/avoid-fats-in-dinner.jpg" alt="Avoid fats in dinner" width="400" height="286" /><br />\r\n<br />\r\nSome people have the habit of fasting the breakfast and lunch instead of intaking more at the dinner. This activity is noticeably erroneous. According to the study, a few hours after charging about 50 80gr fats into &#160;body at dinner, as a result, &#160;the elasticity of blood vessels decreases and increase the risk of &#160;blood clotting. Therefore, individuals should avoid supply your body with too much fast foods for dinner.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n<h3><strong>11. Intake some foods containing fiber before bed at night.</strong></h3>\r\n<div>30 minutes before going to bed, you should provide your body with some snacks with low carbohydrate content which helps you to have a good night. It is the best if you eat some cereal food for serving fiber of which each indivisuals only intake a necessary &#160;half a day.<br />\r\n<br />\r\n<img src="http://localhost/health/uploaded/articles/some-foods-containing-fiber.jpg" alt="Intake some foods containing fiber before bed at night." width="500" height="290" /><br />\r\n&#160;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>', '', 'Eating-habits-to-prevent-disease.jpg', '', NULL, 'Eating habits to prevent disease', 'It is vital for you to have appropriate diets which play an important role in not only balancing the nutrition in your body but also supply full energy for physical activities', '2016-01-28 09:31:24', 0, 75, 4, 1);

